The paper discusses the vulnerability of GPS receivers to signal spoofing attacks and proposes a novel spoofing detection technique. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The implementation and evaluation of the proposed technique involve hardware and software components, which can be classified under systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of GPS in modern smart grids and communication networks, which suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
